        "type": "uofa:IntermediateResult",
        "name": "Synthesis of prior hemolysis modeling studies supporting turbulent stress damage model selection",
        "description": "A comprehensive synthesis of multiple prior studies examining shear-induced hemolysis in rotary blood pumps, including the Giersiepen power-law model, the Bludszuweit tensor formulation, and the Goubergrits-Affeld empirical calibration. This intermediate result aggregates findings from over a decade of benchmark comparisons and consolidates the evidence base justifying selection of the modified power-law hemolysis damage model for centrifugal pump CFD. The synthesis draws on FDA-sponsored round-robin studies, NIH-funded experimental programs, and independent European regulatory submissions, providing the epistemic foundation for turbulence model and damage index parameterization used in the primary validation."
